A suspected robber was shot dead in Lansdowne, Cape Town, on Thursday night. Western Cape police spokesperson W/O Joseph Swartbooi said the suspect was shot after allegedly pointing a firearm at a police officer. He said the Independent Police Investigative  Directorate (Ipid) is investigating. “ [We] confirm that a fleeing robbery suspect was fatally wounded last night [Thursday] in Lansdowne after he pointed a firearm at a police officer,” said Swartbooi. “The circumstances surrounding the death of this suspect are under investigation by Ipid and enquiries are best addressed by their communication department.” TimesLIVE